article.story: TROY, Ala. -- — Tayton Conerway's 15 points helped Troy defeat Old Dominion 86-73 on Thursday night. Conerway shot 5 of 6 from the field and 3 for 3 from the line for the Trojans (8-6, 2-0 Sun Belt Conference). Jackson Fields scored 13 points while shooting 4 for 7 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line, and added seven rebounds and three blocks. Myles Rigsby was 3 of 6 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 6 from the line to finish with 13 points. Devin Ceaser finished with 23 points and four steals for the Monarchs (4-10, 0-3). Tyrone Williams added 22 points and three steals for Old Dominion. Bryce Baker also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
